The first-ever National Climate Task Force meeting was held by National Climate Advisor Gina McCarthy, following President Biden's executive order on climate change. The Task Force is composed of Cabinet-level leaders from 21 federal agencies and senior White House officials. The meeting emphasized the commitment of every agency to collaborate and coordinate efforts to lead the world in clean energy and job creation, while ensuring environmental justice. Vice President Harris also attended the meeting to express her and President Biden's dedication to tackling climate change and supporting agency cooperation. The meeting discussed the Task Force Charter, early actions, priorities, milestones, and the role of the White House Office of Domestic Climate Policy. Task Force members were invited to share how they prioritize climate in decision-making and collaborate with other agencies.